    "recap_headline": "Marshall University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "Buy Tickets Here\n|\nBox Score (PDF)\n|\nChampionship Fund\nHUNTINGTON, W.Va. \u2013\nThe Marshall University Baseball team (9-8, 1-0 SBC) opened Sun Belt Conference play with a 5-2 win over the Georgia State Panthers on Friday evening at Jack Cook Field.\n\"It's great to get the first one of the series and Sun Belt play,\" Herd Baseball Head Coach\nGreg Beals\nsaid. \"I really like how we played. We had competitive at bats. We played great defense. Obviously,\nBryce Blevins\nwas really good today, took us all the way into the ninth inning, and then\nCharlie Krebs\ncame in and did what he did. Got a punch out and an out to shut it down for us. Really good ballgame all the way around and good to be on the winning side.\"\nStarting pitcher\nBryce Blevins\nearned his fourth win of the season with 8.1 innings on the bump allowing just two runs on five hits and a walk with 10 strikeouts.\nCharlie Krebs\ncame on from the bullpen retiring the two batters he faced for his third save of the season.\nAt the plate,\nEvan Bottone\nand\nCooper Hinson\neach had multi-hit contests with\nCleary Simpson\ndriving in two runs.\nThe Herd gave Blevins run support early with a pair of runs in the bottom of the first with Botton scoring on a two-out single by Hinson and\nEthan Murdoch\nscoring\nAJ Havrilla\nwith a two-out double down the right-field line.\nThen in the fifth,\nTyler Kamerer\nand\nJackson Golden\nscored on a Simpson double down the right-field line. Simpson then crossed home on a Havrilla single to center to make it 5-0.\nBlevins had 1-2-3 third, fourth and sixth innings.\nGeorgia State tallied both of its runs in the ninth, but Krebs came on for the final two outs and stranded a runner at second to end the game.\nUP NEXT\nThe Herd is set for game two against the Panthers on Saturday at 4 p.m.\nTo donate to the Championship Fund for Marshall baseball, please click\nHERE\n. All proceeds go directly to the Marshall baseball team.\nPar Mar is the presenting sponsor of the 2026 Marshall baseball team. Par Mar is the official convenience store of Marshall Athletics.\nFor all the latest information about Marshall baseball, follow @herdbaseball on Twitter and Instagram.\nTo follow all Thundering Herd sports and get live stats, schedules and free live audio, download the Marshall Athletics App for iOS and Android.\n---HerdZone.com---"
